Date:11/16/2011 5:17:28 PM
From:Dennis 3
Typically a business selling at a low p/b has low margins and its share price
reflect a low multiple. An 8 ROE is below the avg and it indicates its in a
price competitive business. An 18 ROE is above avg and it indicates the
business is being run correctly and/or has protective moat. Remember to also
look at ROTC along with ROE. High ROE could be gained by taking out a lot of
bank debt.
