GlaxoSmithKline PLC Common Stoc (NYSE: GSK ) - Closed out position

I sold the GSK November $43 calls in June to protect my small gains in this
drug stock. I expect my stock to be called away @ $43 this weekend. I bought
this drug stock in 4/2008 following Buffet's Buys. It has paid a good dividend
(around 5%) but has really gone nowhere in the 3 1/2 years I have owned it. I
booked a 20% profit over this period which only represents a 6% annual return
mostly made up from their dividend payments.

I have not decided where to deploy the proceeds but will probably not reinvest
back into the pharma industry. I think many of the drug stocks can be had at
lower prices (15%-20% lower from current levels).

With my recent sells this year in BMY, COV, LLY and now GSK, my pharma holdings
are about 50% of what they were at the beginning of the year. My drug holdings
now include PFE, BMY, MRK and ABT where they represent 5.5% of my total
combined portfolios (Taxable & IRA). My IRA holds 3x the number drug stock
positions than the taxable account as they continue to be good dividend payers
into the account.

